core/pareto.py — NSGA-II non-dominated sorting + crowding distance:
- Objective dataclass with maximize/minimize sign handling
- fast_non_dominated_sort(): O(MN²) front assignment
- crowding_distance(): diversity preservation within fronts
- pareto_rank(): full pipeline, auto-selects 2-obj or 3-obj mode
- 2D hypervolume indicator
- DEFAULT_OBJECTIVES: affinity, selectivity, synthesizability
- Custom objectives supported via Objective() list

core/de_novo_generator.py — ranking_mode='pareto' option:
- generate_candidates(): ranking_mode + objectives params
- generate_and_screen(): ranking_mode + objectives params
- GeneratedCandidate: pareto_front_idx, pareto_rank, pareto_crowding, pareto_objectives fields
- GenerationResult: ranking_mode, pareto_result fields
- Default mode unchanged (composite) — zero regression

tests/test_pareto.py — 40 tests:
- 7 dominance logic, 7 non-dominated sort, 4 crowding distance
- 7 full pipeline, 3 sign handling, 3 edge cases
- 3 custom objectives, 2 auto-select
- 4 integration (generate_candidates + generate_and_screen)
- 2 regression guards

